      • getChangedTree

        @CheckForNull
 @CheckReturnValue
public TreePath getChangedTree()
        Returns tree which was reparsed by an incremental reparse. When the source file wasn't parsed yet or the parse was a full parse this method returns null.

        Currently the leaf tree is a MethodTree but this may change in the future. Client of this method is responsible to check the corresponding TreeKind to find out if it may perform on the changed subtree or it needs to reprocess the whole tree.

        Returns:
        TreePath or null
        Since:
        0.31

      • getCachedValue

        @CheckForNull
public Object getCachedValue(@NonNull
                                           Object key)
        Retrieve a value cached under the given key using the putCachedValue(java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object, org.netbeans.api.java.source.CompilationInfo.CacheClearPolicy) method.
        Parameters:
        key - for which the cached value should be retrieved
        Returns:
        value originally passed to putCachedValue(java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object, org.netbeans.api.java.source.CompilationInfo.CacheClearPolicy), or null if none
        Since:
        0.90

      • putCachedValue

        public void putCachedValue(@NonNull
                           Object key,
                           @NullAllowed
                           Object value,
                           @NonNull
                           CompilationInfo.CacheClearPolicy clearPolicy)
        Put a value into a cache under the given key. The #clearPolicy parameter specifies the latest time the references to the key and value should be cleared. The infrastructure is free to clear the references at any earlier time. The clients should not depend on this cache for correctness, only to improve performance.
        Parameters:
        key - a unique key under which the value should be stored
        value - the value to store - any value previously set under the same key will be erased from the cache
        clearPolicy - the latest time when the mapping should be cleared from the cache
        Since:
        0.90
